main event: A pilot at Andrews AFB observed a strange object in the sky for approximately 10 seconds.
interesting points: The object was sighted approximately 30 miles away at an altitude of 8000 feet., The object appeared brighter than a typical star but was moving very slowly., Several other lights were observed on the object later., A radar check did not detect the object., It was suggested that the object might have been Venus due to weather conditions.
sighted object: a strange bright object in the sky
witness description: Pilot from Capital Air Lines reported the sighting to GCA Tower.
